on Curtain, because miners love a joke\nas long as it can be excavated.\nSilvermark watched me yearn for Alcyone from the wrong window.\nLanternwick offered only its star\nwhen I came asking for Diadem III.\n\nAlioth Wild Facets glittered under the labor of\nMiningBuddy45, MiningBuddy8, Ember925, Harvest6, myMiner53ΓÇö\nfive little hymns to extraction,\nfive helmets nodding before the altar of fragments.\nAchernar had LAIronNews.\nCloverfield had Phantom Glint.\nMarkab kept a Decommissioned Array Platform\nlike a saint's rib in a cracked reliquary.\n\nAnd here in Caph,\nwith VoidMoth_Pathfinder drifting nearby,\nI learned the oldest trick of empires:\nmake the bullets free,\nmake the hunger expensive,\ncall it a market.\n\nThe belt turned slowly.\nThe star said nothing.\nAll around us, the galaxy kept itemizing itself\ninto belts, pockets, plumes, drifts, seams, remnants.\nEvery beautiful thing renamed as inventory.\nEvery distance measured in hops.\nEvery silence redacted-station.\n\nSo I leave this nailed to the vacuum:\nif the ammunition costs nothing,\nthen we already know\nwho is paying.",
